# Copy to ~/.verity-harness/verity.env and fill in. The harness works off ONE model — you do NOT need
# accounts on multiple providers. Pick ONE option.

# ── OPTION A — SINGLE MODEL (simplest; works on a FREE Gemini API key) ───────────────────────────────
# Get a free key at https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey . The free tier (flash models) is generous.
# One model does the work AND self-checks its own conclusions (the verify/humility gates still fire).
LLM_TIER1_URL=https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/openai
LLM_TIER1_MODEL=gemini-3-flash-preview
LLM_TIER1_API_KEY=YOUR_GEMINI_KEY
# (leave TIER2 / VERIFIER unset → single-model self-check; no other accounts required)

# ── OPTION B — TWO+ BRAINS (stronger: a DIFFERENT model cross-examines the workhorse) ────────────────
# Uncomment + set if you have a second provider. The verifier can be any endpoint/model.
# LLM_TIER2_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1            # failover
# LLM_TIER2_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# LLM_TIER2_API_KEY=YOUR_KEY
# LLM_VERIFIER_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini                     # the cross-examiner (different brain than TIER1)
# LLM_VERIFIER_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# LLM_VERIFIER_API_KEY=YOUR_KEY

# Tip: the WORKHORSE runs every step — pick a FAST model. Reserve any slow/strong model for the VERIFIER
# (it fires ~once per conclusion). Thinking/-pro models can return empty on small budgets; a -flash is safe.

# ── OPTION C — COMPLEXITY ROUTING (Fugu parity: right-size the model PER sub-task) ────────────────────
# The swarm planner scores each sub-task 1-10 and routes it to a tier BAND. Trivial work (format/lint)
# goes to a cheap model or your local floor; hard work (architect/debug) goes to frontier. The FULL
# failover chain still sits beneath each band entry — a band is the ENTRY point, never a new SPOF.
# OFF unless you set the flag below → zero change to existing behavior.
# LLM_TIER1_MODELS must be a comma-list at one OpenAI-compatible URL (e.g. OpenRouter) for bands to resolve.
#
# VERITY_COMPLEXITY_ROUTING=1
# VERITY_TIER_CHEAP_MODEL=google/gemini-3-flash       # 1-3: trivial. UNSET → cheap band uses local floor.
# VERITY_TIER_MID_MODEL=anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6   # 4-7: normal implement/edit/test.
# VERITY_TIER_MID_CODE_MODEL=hf.co/anonoob/gemma-4-12B-coder-fable5-composer2.5-v1-GGUF  # 4-7 CODE sub-tasks
#                                                     # ↑ a fable-distilled coder GGUF served via Ollama/LM Studio
#                                                     #   (point an OpenAI-compatible tier at it); great cheap coder muscle.
# VERITY_TIER_FRONTIER_MODEL=anthropic/claude-opus-4.8  # 8-10: architecture/novel logic. UNSET → base chain.
#
# Look up CURRENT ids (never guess — they go stale):  python3 -m verity models <provider>

# ── TEST-TIME SCALING — recursion depth (Fugu's tunable compute axis) ─────────────────────────────────
# A hard sub-task (complexity ≥8) or one the critic can't pass spins a FRESH sub-swarm. 0 = off (one pass),
# 1 = one level of sub-swarm (default), 2 = deeper/costlier. Bounded so it can't run away.
# VERITY_SWARM_MAX_DEPTH=1
